function [variance,pixarea] = energy2var(energy,numpix,screensz,res,vd)% function [variance,pixarea] = energy2var(energy,numpix,screensz,res,vd)%% computes the contrast variance of an image of a given% contrast energy and size. energy should be expressed in degrees^2% of visual angle.%%% parameters:%% energy-     the contrast energy of the noise field% numpix-	  the total number of pixels in the image% screensz-   a 2 element vector containing the width and %			  height of the screen, respectievely, in cm. %			  (i.e., [width height]).% res-		  a 2 element vector containing the width and %			  height of the screen, respectievely, in pixels. %			  (i.e., [width height]).% vd-		  the viewing distance, in cm.%% output:%% variance-   the contrast variance of the image.% pixarea-    the area of a single pixel, in degrees^2.if nargin == 5		pixarea = (visang(vd,pix2cm(1,screensz,res)))^2;	variance = energy./(numpix*pixarea);else	error('not enough parameters sent.');endreturn;